Answer:

A change requiring updates to AI artifacts is any change to an AI use case that “meaningfully affects the accuracy of the current artifacts,” including, for example:  
a) changing the context, scope, or intended purpose of the use case;  
b) changing the use case’s output or impact on IRS operations;  
c) updating or retraining the underlying AI model(s); or  
d) incorporating new data elements or data sources.
